cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with self-adjusting data structures for answering point location queries in convex and connected subdivisions, which are fundamental problems in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents time and space complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of linear decision trees and logarithmic terms in the time complexity analysis suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
